---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof vs Google Forms — Collect testimonials the right way | SocialProof" description="Google Forms is free but collects testimonials into a spreadsheet. SocialProof turns them into an embeddable widget automatically. Free forever." canonical="https://socialproof.dev/vs/google-forms">
<style>
    body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; margin: 0; background: #fff; color: #111; }
    nav { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 1rem 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; }
    nav a.logo { font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.25rem; color: #111; text-decoration: none; }
    nav .nav-links a { margin-left: 1.5rem; color: #555; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; }
    nav .cta-nav { background: #111; color: #fff !important; padding: .45rem 1rem; border-radius: 6px; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .vs-badge { display: inline-block; background: #f0f0f0; color: #555; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: .35rem .75rem; border-radius: 99px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .hero h1 span { color: #4f46e5; }
    .hero p { font-size: 1.15rem; color: #444; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
    .hero-cta { display: inline-block; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 1rem; }
    .hero-cta:hover { background: #3730a3; }
    .price-callout { display: inline-flex; gap: 2rem; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .price-callout .item { text-align: center; }
    .price-callout .item .price { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; }
    .price-callout .item .label { font-size: 0.85rem; color: #777; margin-top: .2rem; }
    .price-callout .item.vouch .price { color: #4f46e5; }
    .price-callout .item.other .price { color: #888; }
    section { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 2rem; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .compare-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .compare-table th { padding: .75rem 1rem; text-align: left; font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .05em; color: #888; border-bottom: 2px solid #eee; }
    .compare-table th:nth-child(2) { color: #4f46e5; }
    .compare-table td { padding: .85rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #f0f0f0; font-size: 0.97rem; vertical-align: top; }
    .compare-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .compare-table td:first-child { color: #555; font-weight: 500; }
    .yes { color: #16a34a; font-weight: 600; }
    .no { color: #dc2626; font-weight: 600; }
    .partial { color: #d97706; font-weight: 600; }
    .winner-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .winner-card { border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.75rem; }
    .winner-card.vouch { background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #86efac; }
    .winner-card.other { background: #fafafa; border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; }
    .winner-card h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 .75rem; }
    .winner-card ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
    .winner-card li { font-size: 0.92rem; color: #444; margin-bottom: .4rem; }
    .flow-steps { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
    .flow-card { border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #e5e5e5; }
    .flow-card h3 { margin: 0 0 1rem; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .05em; color: #888; }
    .flow-card ol { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
    .flow-card li { font-size: 0.92rem; color: #444; margin-bottom: .5rem; line-height: 1.5; }
    .flow-card.vouch { border-color: #86efac; background: #f0fdf4; }
    .flow-card.vouch h3 { color: #16a34a; }
    .bottom-cta { text-align: center; background: #4f46e5; color: #fff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 3.5rem 2rem; margin: 3rem 0; }
    .bottom-cta h2 { color: #fff; font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .bottom-cta p { color: #c7d2fe; max-width: 500px; margin: 0 auto 2rem; }
    .bottom-cta a { display: inline-block; background: #fff; color: #4f46e5; padding: .85rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
    footer { text-align: center; padding: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; color: #aaa; font-size: 0.85rem; }
    footer a { color: #aaa; margin: 0 .5rem; }
    @media (max-width: 600px) { .winner-grid, .flow-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .price-callout { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; } }
</style>
<nav>
  <a href="/" class="logo">SocialProof</a>
  <div class="nav-links">
    <a href="/vs">Compare</a>
    <a href="/for">Industries</a>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="cta-nav">Try free →</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <span class="vs-badge">SocialProof vs Google Forms</span>
  <h1>Testimonials in a spreadsheet vs <span>on your website</span></h1>
  <p>Google Forms collects your testimonials and dumps them in a spreadsheet. SocialProof collects them, helps you approve them, and shows them on your site — automatically.</p>
  <div class="price-callout">
    <div class="item vouch">
      <div class="price">Free</div>
      <div class="label">SocialProof — forever</div>
    </div>
    <div class="item other">
      <div class="price">Free</div>
      <div class="label">Google Forms — spreadsheet only</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="hero-cta">Try SocialProof free →</a>
</div>

<section>
  <h2>Both are free. Here's what's different.</h2>
  <table class="compare-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Feature</th>
        <th>SocialProof</th>
        <th>Google Forms</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Collects testimonials</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes — purpose-built</td>
        <td class="partial">Yes — generic form</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Where responses go</td>
        <td class="yes">SocialProof dashboard — ready to approve</td>
        <td class="no">Google Sheets spreadsheet</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Embeddable widget for your website</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes — one line of code</td>
        <td class="no">No — manual copy/paste required</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Approval workflow</td>
        <td class="yes">Approve before it goes live</td>
        <td class="no">No — everything goes to spreadsheet</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Star ratings structure</td>
        <td class="yes">Built-in — structured automatically</td>
        <td class="partial">Manual setup, no native star field</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Responder name + photo</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes — structured fields</td>
        <td class="partial">Manual field setup</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Display on your site without code</td>
        <td class="yes">Yes</td>
        <td class="no">No — requires developer or Zapier</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Time from link to live on site</td>
        <td class="yes">~2 minutes</td>
        <td class="no">Hours (export → format → code → embed)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Google account required</td>
        <td class="yes">No — works for everyone</td>
        <td class="partial">Recommended for full features</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>The workflow difference is everything</h2>
  <div class="flow-steps">
    <div class="flow-card other">
      <h3>Google Forms workflow</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Build a form with custom fields</li>
        <li>Customer submits → goes to Google Sheets</li>
        <li>You open the spreadsheet</li>
        <li>Copy the good ones manually</li>
        <li>Paste into your website editor</li>
        <li>Format it to look like a testimonial</li>
        <li>Repeat for every new testimonial</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="flow-card vouch">
      <h3>SocialProof workflow</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Share your collection link</li>
        <li>Customer submits</li>
        <li>You click "Approve" in your dashboard</li>
        <li>It appears on your site automatically</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>When Google Forms makes sense — and when it doesn't</h2>
  <div class="winner-grid">
    <div class="winner-card vouch">
      <h3>✅ Use SocialProof when you want to…</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Display testimonials on your website automatically</li>
        <li>Control what's visible before it goes live</li>
        <li>Avoid copying and pasting from a spreadsheet</li>
        <li>Look professional without paying extra</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="winner-card other">
      <h3>📋 Stick with Google Forms if you…</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Only need a private record (not public display)</li>
        <li>Are already doing complex Google Workspace workflows</li>
        <li>Have a developer who can wire up a custom display</li>
        <li>Collect many different types of data in one form</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <p style="color:#444; font-size:1.05rem; line-height:1.7;">The bottom line: Google Forms is a workhorse. It'll collect your testimonials. But the moment you want to <em>show</em> them on your website, you're on your own. SocialProof was built for that specific gap — the part Google Forms doesn't do.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="bottom-cta">
    <h2>Collect. Approve. Display. Done.</h2>
    <p>SocialProof closes the loop Google Forms leaves open. Free forever for 1 active widget.</p>
    <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup">Get started free →</a>
  </div>
</section>

<footer>
  <a href="/">SocialProof</a>
  <a href="/vs">All comparisons</a>
  <a href="/for">Industries</a>
  <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
  <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
  <p style="margin-top:1rem;">© 2025 SocialProof. Free testimonial tool for small businesses.</p>
</footer>
</Base>
